REPLACE INTO starships (slug,name,craft,affiliation,type,category,scale,length,skill,crew,crewSkill,passengers,cargoCapacity,consumables,cost,hyperdrive,navComputer,maneuverability,space,atmosphere,hull,shields,sensors,weapons,description,imageFilename,imageUrl,notes,sources,pageId,revisionId) VALUES ('cec-dse-30-m-starlight-class-deep-space-explorer','CEC DSE-30/M Starlight Class Deep Space Explorer',NULL,NULL,'Stock light freighter','transport','Starfighter','63.5 meters',NULL,'5','Astrogation 3D, (s)Space Transports: DSE-30 4D','30','200 MT','1 year','782,500',NULL,'Yes','0D','4','70; 100 kmh','8D','1D','{"passive":"30/1D","scan":"60/2D+1","search":"120/3D+2","focus":"4/4D"}','[]','The CEC DSE-30 is a holdover from a long gone era of galactic exploration. Originally built to explore new space lanes and develop trade routes during the glory days of the Old Republic. Back then, CEC’s market strategy fed upon new space lanes and dependable ships. The production of the DSE-30 design dwindled as expansion of the Republic. Even if the most horrible of circumstances occur with deep space exploration, the ship’s two escape pods and a hypertransceiver dramatically increase the survivability ratios for the crew. Recently CEC officials have decided to pull this old design out of mothballs and start production again. The CEC DES-30/M possesses upgraded weapons and engine systems. While its original exploration is no longer of great concern, growing instability in the galaxy has led to the market for a long range transport with more space for cargo and personnel than the YT series possesses. The extra space allotted to sensor and communications equipment (leftover from the original exploration specs) also makes this ship popular as a covert communications and command ship for both Rebel and Imperial forces. And, like the YT series, this ship can be upgraded and modified quite extensively to suit the needs of the owner.',NULL,NULL,'Source text CC-BY-SA 3.0 from http://d6holocron.com/wiki/CEC%20DSE-30%2FM%20Starlight%20Class%20Deep%20Space%20Explorer','["http://d6holocron.com/wiki/CEC%20DSE-30%2FM%20Starlight%20Class%20Deep%20Space%20Explorer"]',5315,9021);
REPLACE INTO starships (slug,name,craft,affiliation,type,category,scale,length,skill,crew,crewSkill,passengers,cargoCapacity,consumables,cost,hyperdrive,navComputer,maneuverability,space,atmosphere,hull,shields,sensors,weapons,description,imageFilename,imageUrl,notes,sources,pageId,revisionId) VALUES ('cl-12-outrider','CL-12 “Outrider”','Kaeron Industrial Cartel CL-12 “Outrider”',NULL,'Light Scout/Starfighter','transport','Starfighter','8.8 meters','Starfighter piloting: CL-12','1','Varies','None.','35 kg','2 days','140,000 (new), 75,000 (used)',NULL,'Limited to 2 jumps','3D+1','9','400; 1,150 km/h','2D','1D','{"passive":"25/1D","scan":"40/2D","search":"70/3D","focus":"3/4D+1"}','[{"name":"2 Light Laser Cannons","fireArc":"Front","skill":"Starship gunnery","fireControl":"2D","spaceRange":"1-3/10/20","atmosphereRange":"100-300/1/2 km","damage":"4D"},{"name":"1 Light Ion Cannon","fireArc":"Front","skill":"Starship gunnery","fireControl":"1D","spaceRange":"1-3/7/36","atmosphereRange":"100-300/700/3.6 km","damage":"3D+2"}]','The CL-12 Outrider is a small, dart-shaped craft, nearly nine meters in length. The cockpit is small and cramped, even for a diminutive pilot. The canopy is bubble-shaped, providing excellent visibility in all directions. Three KIC vectored ion engines dominate the rear half of the fuselage.The CL-12 was designed and manufactured as a light scout craft, and marketed towards local security forces, with which it was quite popular. Unsurprisingly, it is also popular amongst pirates and mercenaries. Although blessed with high speed and maneuverability, it is by no means a rugged craft. Many pilots complain that the CL-12 sees more maintenance than flight time, but the additional care is required to keep the power system and shield generators running smoothly. In addition to its speed, the CL-12 is gifted with a top-notch Xelandran sensor system.',NULL,NULL,'Source text CC-BY-SA 3.0 from http://d6holocron.com/wiki/CL-12%20%E2%80%9COutrider%E2%80%9D','["http://d6holocron.com/wiki/CL-12%20%E2%80%9COutrider%E2%80%9D"]',573,10917);
REPLACE INTO starships (slug,name,craft,affiliation,type,category,scale,length,skill,crew,crewSkill,passengers,cargoCapacity,consumables,cost,hyperdrive,navComputer,maneuverability,space,atmosphere,hull,shields,sensors,weapons,description,imageFilename,imageUrl,notes,sources,pageId,revisionId) VALUES ('cr20-republic-carrier','CR20 Republic Carrier','Corellian Engineering Corp. CR20 Light Cruiser','General / Old Republic','Troop carrier','transport','Capital','60 meters','Capital ship piloting: Republic Carrier','6','Astrogation 3D, capital ship piloting 4D+2, capital ship shields 3D+1, sensors 3D+2','40 (troops)','50 metric tons','2 months','680,000 credits (265,000 used)',NULL,'Yes','2D','5','295; 850 km/h','3D+1','2D+1','{"passive":"25/1D+1","scan":"50/2D","search":"75/2D+2","focus":"3/3D"}','[{"name":"2 Double Turbolaser Cannons","fireArc":"Turret (left and right)","skill":"Capital Ship Gunnery","fireControl":"1D+2","spaceRange":"1-8/17/60","atmosphereRange":"100-800/1.7/6 km","damage":"3D+2"}]','The CR-20 troop carrier was a type of transport ship used to deploy small units of clone troopers. The CR-20 troop carrier was armed with two double turbolaser cannons. It was sixty meters long and could carry up to forty clone troopers, twelve 74-Z speeder bikes, and their corresponding supplies. The carrier''s crew consisted of two pilots, one communications officer, and three engineers. Originally designed by the Corellian Engineering Corporation for use by its security forces, the Republic purchased surplus CR-20s one standard month after the First Battle of Geonosis. Despite this, they were widely unseen in the Republic Navy early in the Clone Wars. It was not until the Battle of JanFathal, where Anakin Skywalker piloted a CIS-owned CR-20 to rescue Republic Intelligence operative Hallena Devis, that the usefulness of the CR-20 Troop Carrier became evident. Generally, they were used in situations where the large Acclamator-class assault ships were impractical or unneeded.','cr20.jpg',NULL,'Source text CC-BY-SA 3.0 from http://d6holocron.com/wiki/CR20%20Republic%20Carrier','["http://d6holocron.com/wiki/CR20%20Republic%20Carrier"]',5679,51229);
